## Essential Context

- `window.__domRacerDebug` must not exist in source/build.
- Centralized tuning: `gameConfig.ts` groups (TIMING, TOAST, COINS, SPECIALS, EFFECTS, JACKPOT, POLICE, PLANE, ENCOUNTER, OVERGROWTH, NEAR_MISS, OBJECTIVES, PLAYER). All runtime files import these groups directly.
- `gameRuntime.ts` is a lean utility module: `cloneWorld`, `clonePickup`, `cloneRect`, `randomBetween`, `blendAngle`, `shufflePickups`, `isSpecialPickup`, `pickSpecialEffect`, `adaptBlackoutEffectForSurface`, `getFlavorText`, special/vehicle accessors, showcase data. No re-exports.
- `SurfaceSample` interface lives in `gameStateTypes.ts` (not gameRuntime).
- `ShowcaseTheme` interface + `SHOWCASE_THEMES` data live in `gameRuntime.ts`.
- Police chase lifecycle (`resolvePoliceChaseTickStep`) is in `encounterRuntime.ts` with event-based side-effect dispatch.
- 8 special effects: bonus, magnet, invert, ghost, blackout, cooldown, lure, jackpot.
- 5 airplane drop modes: bonus drop, coin trail, spotlight, lucky wind, police delay.
- Sprite files in `src/game/sprites/`; consumers import from barrel `./sprites`.
- Scanner classifies `img`, `picture`, `video`, `canvas` as `ice`; `svg` as `boost`; YouTube/Vimeo iframes as `ice`.
- ESLint + Prettier configured. Scripts: `lint`, `lint:fix`, `format`, `format:check`.
- 79 smoke tests across 8 files. `npm run test` / `npm run build` must pass.

